title: Our Staff
content:
## Landry Langley - Executive Director Howdy! My name is Landry Landry and I am a junior Animal Science major from Palestine, Texas. But most importantly I am the loudest and proudest member of the Fighting Texas Aggie Class of 2026 A-A-A WHOOP! In my free time, I enjoy spending time with friends, attending any Texas A&M sports event, random car rides, shopping at Costco, and karaoke:). My favorite A&M tradition is Aggie Bonfire. Paying respect to the lives lost and supporting each other just because we are the Aggie family.
![](/images/uploads/dsc_0711.jpeg)
## Andrew Parker - Director of Engagement Howdy my name is Andrew Parker and I’m a junior materials science engineering major from Plano, Texas. But most importantly, I am the loudest and the proudest member of the Fighting Texas Aggie Class of 2026 (A-A-A WHOOP)! I have the honor of serving as the Director of Engagement for FEAST this year. My job is to manage the BIGS program which aims to connect the FEAST alumni with the incoming FEAST freshman through hangouts and events. In my free time I like working out, playing intramural sports, and supporting my fellow Aggies at sports and traditions! My favorite A&M tradition is Muster because it serves as a time to mourn and celebrate the lives of fallen Aggies in camaraderie with your fellow students, family, and friends as well as the reunion class.
![](/images/uploads/dsc_0731.jpeg)
## Oliver Kennedy - Director of Finance Howdy! My name is Oliver Kennedy and I am an industrial distribution major and a Masters in Science in Finance student from Sugar Land, TX. But most importantly I am the loudest and the proudest member of the fighting texas aggie class of 2026 A-A-A-WHOOP! In my free time I enjoy fishing, participating in intramurals, playing basketball at the rec, and watching all the A&M sporting events. My favorite A&M tradition is aggie muster and how we honor all the aggies who have passed away within the past year. I find it meaningful how we remember all of our aggies graduated or not.
![](/images/uploads/dsc_0727.jpeg)
## Ella Sanders - Director of Marketing Howdy! My name is Ella Sanders and I am a junior nursing major from Dallas, Texas. But more importantly, I am THE loudest and THE proudest member of the Fightin' Texas Aggie Class of 2026! A A A WHOOP!!! In my free time, I enjoy hanging out with friends, cooking and baking, and watching football. My favorite Aggie tradition is Muster, because it allows us to celebrate all the lives of Aggies that have passed that year, as well as the hear from the reunion class. It is amazing to hear how different but yet the same Texas A&M is from 50 years ago. Knowing that our university cares about each and every one of it's students and that our names will one day be called is so special to me.
![](/images/uploads/dsc_0719.jpeg)

## Dylan Brunner - 12th Man Howdy! My name is Dylan Brunner and I am a sophomore Mechanical & Manufacturing Engineering Technology major from The Woodlands, Texas. But most importantly, I am the loudest and the proudest member of the Fighting Texas Aggie Class of 2027(A-A-A-A-A). In my free time I enjoy playing intramural sports, building legos, playing rocket league, and … My favorite A&M tradition is Bonfire Remembrance, because it is such a surreal experience standing by the memorial at 2:42am with your fellow aggies to honor the 12 that passed away that day.
![](/images/uploads/dsc_0696.jpeg)

I love scuba diving, working out, and country music! My favorite A&M tradition is Fish Camp because it introduces new Aggies to the traditions and family they’ll find in Aggieland!

## Jackson Hurd - Functions Howdy! My name is Jackson Hurd and I am an Accounting major from Arlington, Texas, but most importantly, I am THE loudest and THE proudest member of the Fighting Texas Aggie Class of 2027, A-A-A-A-A!!!!! I am an avid rap, r&b, and country music listener. In my free time I love to go to the gym and grill for my friends and family. My favorite Aggie tradition is Silver Taps. This is tradition is profoundly solemn, it is definitely a required experience to have while you’re at Texas A&M.
![](/images/uploads/dsc_0684.jpeg)

My favorite tradition at Texas A&M is Silver Taps because its shows the camaraderie that unites Texas A&M and shows respect to our fallen.
